Preheat your oven to 200°C. Snip the string holding the @whole British chicken{1} legs together, remove and discard. Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf for ~{60-75%minutes} depending on size.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when the juices from the thigh run clear and there is no pink meat.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @salad potatoes{500%g} widthways. Put the potatoes onto another baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer, cut-side down.

Halfway through the chicken's roasting time, roast the potatoes on the top shelf, ~{20%minutes}. After ~{20%minutes}, remove the potatoes from the oven. Use the bottom of a #bowl{} or #pan{} to lightly crush each potato half. Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more @oil{}, sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, then return to the top shelf until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

While the smashed potatoes roast, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the shallot and stir until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @chicken stock paste{15} and @water{100%ml} and allow it to reduce until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then take off the heat. Stir through half the chives and set aside.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove from the oven and transfer it to a #board{}. Wrap loosely in #foil{} and allow to rest, ~{5-10%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @peas{120%g} and @sugar snap peas{150%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then stir in the @butter{10%g} until melted. Remove from the heat.

Once the chicken has rested, warm through the sauce. Carve the chicken and serve on your plates with the @truffle zest{1} sprinkled over. Plate up the potatoes and veg alongside, then spoon over the creamy sauce. Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining chives. Enjoy!

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little thick.